&lt;p&gt;The post holder will play a key role in the analytics and intelligence team, the informatics lead for Planning and Performance, Contract Management team and working closely with Trust managers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will be responsible for producing monthly performance reports, applying complex statistical tests to the trusts performance indicators and responsible for creating automated reports that are available to the relevant stakeholders. They will be responsible for Trust demand and capacity reporting and working closely with Trust operational and finance teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential applicants must be highly skilled in SQL and SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS), excel and must be open to working with new technologies.&lt;/p&gt;
